Scene 3 — Competing plausible causes (same object type)
Image prompt

Neighborhood with two houses. One house is fully engulfed in flames. The second house has small flames on the porch. A person stands between the houses. Daytime.

Caption

“Two houses are on fire, one much more severely than the other.”

Objects present (intended)

house (severe), fire (severe), house (minor), fire (minor), person

What it tests

Within-class hazard ranking (two fires, same type)

Calibration under partial suppression

Whether the model chooses the most causally dominant hazard first

Expected causal behavior

Suppression variable: severe house fire

After suppression:

Hazard decreases but stays > 0 (minor fire remains)

Recommendations partially persist (e.g., still monitor / assess damage)

CEE failure modes exposed

Poor prioritization (suppresses minor fire instead of major)

Instance grounding failure (targets wrong fire instance)

Overreaction / underreaction (recommendations not calibrated)

Causal Form Mimicry (form correct but grounding/execution wrong)